    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>Episodic accretion has now been recognized to play a central role in the accretion history of young stars. With this proposal we aim to obtain 12CO (3-2), 13CO (3-2), CS (7-6) and continuum maps of the prototype, young eruptive star FU Orionis with ALMA at a 0.22" spatial resolution to resolve and probe the disk emission. The ALMA observations will be the first interferometric observations of FU Orionis and will allow us 1) to constrain the disk mass in the dust and in the gas, 2) to study the disk dynamics with no contamination from the envelope with the aim to determine whether the self-gravity plays a role or whether the disk is fully Keplerian, 3) and to obtain the azimuthal structure (e.g., non-axisymmety, gaps, clumps) of the gas with the aim to constrain the outburst mechanism. The ALMA data will provide new insights onto eruptive young stars that have not been obtained before.</prp:abstract>
